<div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12">
        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Eclipse'); ?>
        <p><strong>Eclipse</strong> is an Integrated Development Environment (<?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('IDE', 'ITS'); ?>).</p>
        <p>It contains a base workspace and an extensible plug-in system for customizing the environment.</p>
        <p>Written mostly in <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Java', 'L'); ?>, Eclipse can be used to develop applications.</p>
        <p>By means of various plug-ins, Eclipse may also be used to develop applications in other programming languages: <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Ada', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('C', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('C++', 'LC'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('COBOL', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Fortran', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Haskell', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('JavaScript', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Perl', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('PHP', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Prolog', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Python', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('R', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Ruby', 'L'); ?> (including Ruby on Rails framework), <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Scala', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Clojure', 'L'); ?>, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Groovy', 'L'); ?> and <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Erlang', 'L'); ?>.</p>
        <p>Development environments include the Eclipse Java development tools (JDT) for Java and Scala, Eclipse CDT for C/C++ and Eclipse PDT for PHP, among others.</p>
        <p>The initial codebase originated from <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('IBM', 'C'); ?> <strong>VisualAge</strong>.</p>
        <p>The Eclipse software development kit (SDK), which includes the Java development tools, is meant for Java developers.</p>
        <p>Users can extend its abilities by installing plug-ins written for the Eclipse Platform, such as development toolkits for other programming languages, and can write and contribute their own plug-in modules.</p>
    </div>
